<div class="modal fade" id="cerenaModal" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="cerenaModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
    <div class="modal-dialog">
        <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header" style="border: none; padding: 10px 10px 0 0;">
                <button type="button" class="btn-close" data-bs-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close"></button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body text-dark">
                Cerena Chaney is a native of Ponca City, Oklahoma. Dance has been her passion for as long as she can remember. Cerena began dancing at the age of three and continued to dance under the direction of Fran Norris at Miss Fran’s Dance and Tumbling Studio until graduating high school. Her love for this art form quickly grew into a permanent part of her life.
                <br><br>
                After graduating high school, Cerena wanted to take her passion to the next level, and she attended Oklahoma City University as a dance major. While at Oklahoma City University, she continued her love of dance technique and performance, but also fostered a passion for teaching dance to others. Cerena graduated in May 2020 with a Bachelor of Science in Dance Pedagogy.
                <br><br>
                Since graduating, Cerena has continued to teach, learn, and grow in her love of dance. She is starting her fifth year working for American Dance Drill Team, teaching dance team camps during the summer months to high school dance teams across the Midwest. Cerena is excited to start her second year as a dance teacher at Classen SAS Middle School. She is also starting her first year as the Head Pom Coach at Classen SAS High School and Classen SAS Middle School. Cerena is so excited to be starting her fourth year at Dance Unlimited, and she can’t wait to continue teaching, growing, and building relationships with students and families!
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
